  "body": "### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nAccording to the documentation (https://quarkus.io/guides/lifecycle):\r\n\r\n\"A bean represented by a class, producer method or field annotated with `@Startup` is initialized at application startup:\"\r\n\r\nFrom this it seems that annotating the `@Produces` method with `@Startup` will make the bean be created at startup.\r\nUsing the `@Startup` annotation does create the bean. However, it throws a warning during compilation:\r\n\r\n`[WARNING] [io.quarkus.arc.deployment.StartupBuildSteps] Ignored an invalid @Startup method declared on ...`\r\n\r\nIdeally I would like the startup to be valid on producers.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\n`@Startup` + `@Produces` creates the bean at startup and no warning is given during compilation.\r\n\r\n### Actual behavior\r\n\r\n`@Startup` + `@Produces` creates the bean at startup, but a warning is given during compilation.\r\n\r\n### How to Reproduce?\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### Output of `uname -a` or `ver`\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### Output of `java -version`\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### Quarkus version or git rev\r\n\r\n3.8.3\r\n\r\n### Build tool (ie. output of `mvnw --version` or `gradlew --version`)\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### Additional information\r\n\r\n_No response_",
